WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.707
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.707 --> 00:00:02.754
Praise the Lord.

00:00:02.754 --> 00:00:04.400
Thank you for joining us today.

00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:08.436
Well, we want to take the time right now just to thank all our servicemen and women.

00:00:08.436 --> 00:00:12.011
I know a lot of you don't get enough appreciation.

00:00:12.011 --> 00:00:24.720
I feel in my heart there's a lot of you that are still going through the trials of war, from your body being mangled up to all kinds of things.

00:00:24.720 --> 00:00:33.376
You know, there's men that have lost their wives, there's women that have lost their husbands, and fathers and mothers that have lost their sons and daughters.

00:00:33.376 --> 00:00:38.124
And I want to just take the time to say thank you.

00:00:38.124 --> 00:00:38.529
Thank you.

00:00:38.934 --> 00:00:43.850
Thank you for sacrificing your life to make America great.

00:00:43.850 --> 00:00:46.982
Because of people like you, we're free.

00:00:46.982 --> 00:01:02.884
Because of people like you that have fought in those trenches, and went and got drafted in Vietnam, and all the terrible things of war, the things that you have seen, we pray peace over you today.

00:01:02.884 --> 00:01:07.028
We pray peace over your mind today.

00:01:07.028 --> 00:01:11.531
We pray peace that passes all understanding over you.

00:01:11.531 --> 00:01:19.360
I know there's a lot of you; you email me and you tell me, "I'm battling with PTSD, and I have nightmares every night.

00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:24.034
" And my goodness, I pray peace over you.

00:01:24.034 --> 00:01:37.676
We know your sacrifice was great, and many people will never understand that sacrifice because they've not walked it.

00:01:37.676 --> 00:01:41.680
And so we just want to take the time to say thank you.

00:01:41.680 --> 00:01:43.497
Thank you for our country.

00:01:43.497 --> 00:01:45.760
Thank you for fighting for us.

00:01:45.760 --> 00:01:47.973
Because of you, we're not speaking another language.

00:01:47.973 --> 00:01:52.020
We're Americans and we just want to say thank you.

00:01:52.020 --> 00:01:52.240
God bless you.

00:01:52.679 --> 00:01:57.260
So, we're going to go over some of the things that we spoke about last time in the last video.

00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:00.576
You know, folks, I believe in God for big.

00:02:00.576 --> 00:02:02.544
That is my motto.

00:02:02.544 --> 00:02:05.300
It's what I teach my kids.

00:02:05.300 --> 00:02:06.347
That's what I teach.

00:02:06.347 --> 00:02:09.440
That's what my wife and I—we don't want to think small.

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:13.246
You know, it's like Oral Roberts said, "Make no little plans here.

00:02:13.246 --> 00:02:15.360
" It's all over his campus.

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:17.931
"Make no little plans here.

00:02:17.931 --> 00:02:18.959
Think big.

00:02:18.959 --> 00:02:19.268
Think big.

00:02:19.576 --> 00:02:22.520
" So when you drive around, it's like Oral Roberts University.

00:02:22.520 --> 00:02:23.663
You can go there so many times.

00:02:23.663 --> 00:02:24.1000
I go out there all the time.

00:02:24.1000 --> 00:02:32.730
Drive by every day almost and look at the campus because it inspires me to think and believe big—that that was somebody's faith, you know.

00:02:32.730 --> 00:02:47.080
And so when I talk about driving around cars, I really don't have a desire to have a fleet load of cars, but I think that's the best the world has to offer: Cadillacs, Range Rovers.

00:02:47.080 --> 00:02:49.599
That's what the Hollywood movie stars drive, you know.

00:02:49.599 --> 00:02:52.736
And, you know, we don't have a Rolls-Royce dealership or Ferrari.

00:02:52.736 --> 00:02:57.573
I drive around in those to inspire yourself to think bigger.

00:02:57.573 --> 00:03:16.213
When you're raised in poverty, when you're raised in what I was raised in, you don't have an inward image of wealth to think bigger for God to do bigger because you're so used to thinking small.

00:03:16.213 --> 00:03:21.486
You know, grandma was poor, her grandma was poor, everybody's been poor, and you'll be poor, too.

00:03:21.486 --> 00:03:23.570
No, I'm redeemed from the curse.

00:03:23.570 --> 00:03:26.533
And I believe poverty is a curse, regardless.

00:03:26.906 --> 00:03:32.674
I've never seen anybody that's not able to pay their bills, struggling and eating Spam and doing things.

00:03:32.674 --> 00:03:33.840
Well, people say, "I like Spam.

00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:34.710
" Well, I don't.

00:03:34.710 --> 00:03:34.1000
I don't.

00:03:35.289 --> 00:03:35.579
I personally don't.

00:03:36.479 --> 00:03:37.440
That's my opinion.

00:03:37.440 --> 00:03:47.759
So you know, you have people that are raised on certain things—Ramen noodles and things that you go, "Well, that's all we had because that's what we could afford.

00:03:47.759 --> 00:03:51.073
" Living on food stamps, living on these things.

00:03:51.073 --> 00:03:52.239
That's a curse.

00:03:52.239 --> 00:03:54.164
True poverty is a curse.

00:03:54.164 --> 00:03:55.702
It's not a blessing.

00:03:55.702 --> 00:04:09.074
And people, you live in some of these remote areas in Haiti and Africa and in Asia or whatever, and you're living in a tin hut or whatever—that's not a blessing.

00:04:09.074 --> 00:04:13.428
I look at what everybody goes to work for Monday through Friday.

00:04:13.428 --> 00:04:27.610
The reason I say it, and I'm so strong about it, is because we all go to work every day to try to make the dream, to get enough money to put your kids through college, to pay your bills on time so they don't repo your car.

00:04:27.610 --> 00:04:31.613
I've been there, and I know that those times were sorrowful.

00:04:31.613 --> 00:04:33.188
That was hard.

00:04:33.188 --> 00:04:43.405
And believing God to get extra, selling on eBay and Poshmark and doing these things that we've done, stepping out by faith and finding things.

00:04:43.405 --> 00:04:48.340
There's even another level of, I see, wealth.

00:04:48.340 --> 00:04:55.554
And the Bible says, "Beloved, I wish above all things that you prosper and be in health, even as your soul prospers.

00:04:55.554 --> 00:04:59.326
" There's so much in the Bible about walking in abundance.

00:04:59.326 --> 00:05:02.320
In abundance to the full, till it overflows.

00:05:02.320 --> 00:05:05.109
Not living barely getting by and broke.

00:05:05.109 --> 00:05:23.680
And yeah, people got you burned out because of the prosperity preaching and all that stuff, but I believe a lot of them started out good, trying to help out the body of Christ to break off the yoke of bondage, because I'm telling you, there's a lot of bondage with poverty.

00:05:23.680 --> 00:05:33.772
And I'm not saying that there's no bondage with prosperity, because there are a lot of people that lose themselves in it, and it is what it is.

00:05:34.864 --> 00:05:42.617
But I think there's a happy medium that you can have blessing as long as the blessing doesn't have you.

00:05:42.617 --> 00:05:52.090
So, that's what I'm talking about: getting that inward image of the blessing and walking in an abundance so you can help those around you.

00:05:52.090 --> 00:05:53.371
Help those around you.

00:05:53.668 --> 00:06:04.564
I've seen people—man, I wish, you know, you drive by and you see somebody that they don't have nothing, you're looking at them going, "Man, I wish I had a little extra to help them out.

00:06:04.564 --> 00:06:12.263
" But there's so much blockage in the mind when it comes to the devil trying to tell you you can't have nothing.

00:06:12.263 --> 00:06:14.560
He doesn't wrestle with you trying to bless you.

00:06:15.493 --> 00:06:17.200
You know what happened with me?

00:06:17.200 --> 00:06:18.480
Let me tell you.

00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:21.039
I'll be real with you right now.

00:06:21.039 --> 00:06:28.970
Satan himself came to my house, and I used the visions that I have—he showed me all the wealth.

00:06:28.970 --> 00:06:36.533
He said, "If you bow your knee to me, if you bow your knee to me, I will give you all this wealth.

00:06:36.533 --> 00:06:40.820
" I saw jets, I saw houses, I saw Ferraris, I saw all this.

00:06:40.820 --> 00:06:50.891
He said, "If you serve me and use the gift that you have for seeing for the kingdom of darkness, I will give you everything that your heart's desire.

00:06:59.968 --> 00:07:00.293
" He showed it all to me.

00:07:03.199 --> 00:07:14.319
I saw his palace, and it was black onyx, and blood was flowing from his throne, and it was just similar to what happened, I believe, to what happened to Jesus: "If you serve me, I'll give you all this.

00:07:14.319 --> 00:07:19.372
I'll give you the kingdoms of the earth.

00:07:20.319 --> 00:07:31.573
" To make a long story short, because I don't like talking about the darkness, there's nothing the devil has to offer in all that that I wanted.

00:07:47.288 --> 00:07:47.523
I want the anointing.

00:07:52.090 --> 00:07:52.360
I want the presence of the Father.

00:07:52.900 --> 00:07:53.947
And in Him, there's peace.

00:07:53.947 --> 00:07:54.707
There's joy.

00:07:54.707 --> 00:08:01.141
There's all those things.

00:08:04.624 --> 00:08:05.152
The devil has nothing good to offer.

00:08:05.152 --> 00:08:07.421
I've had, what, three visitations like that.

00:08:07.670 --> 00:08:11.315
The last one was to challenge the Word.

00:08:22.080 --> 00:08:22.364
And he spoke to me, and I said, "Are you coming to offer the kingdoms again?

00:08:22.933 --> 00:08:23.786
" And he said, "No.

00:08:23.786 --> 00:08:28.925
Once you reject me once, I never come and offer you anything again.

00:08:36.867 --> 00:08:37.164
I'm coming to challenge the Word.

00:08:37.164 --> 00:08:41.211
" You know, like I said, I don't talk about the darkness.

00:08:41.211 --> 00:08:47.920
But I want you to know that even the devil tries to entice people with wealth.

00:08:47.920 --> 00:08:48.640
Why?

00:08:48.640 --> 00:08:51.129
Because it's what the world wants.

00:09:04.080 --> 00:09:04.240
We wake up every day, Monday through Friday, like I said.

00:09:04.240 --> 00:09:10.560
But how much can you be a believing believer and have it, and show the world that you can have Jesus and the blessing?

00:09:13.205 --> 00:09:13.530
You can have Jesus and the blessing.

00:09:13.530 --> 00:09:29.657
So, that's not my message for today, but I feel like a lot of people are hung up on poverty, and I refuse to take that vow.

00:09:29.657 --> 00:09:32.600
I refuse to take it for my kids.

00:09:32.600 --> 00:09:33.804
I want generational wealth.

00:09:46.297 --> 00:09:46.560
I'm believing for what He showed me about the cryptocurrencies.

00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:54.951
I'm believing for what He showed me about gold and silver, and what He showed me about these things.

00:10:01.040 --> 00:10:01.600
And I'm standing on what the Lord has showed me.

00:10:04.970 --> 00:10:09.251
I stand on that.

00:10:09.251 --> 00:10:12.800
Now, everything the Lord does, it's like I told Dino.

00:10:12.800 --> 00:10:17.239
We were talking about the anointing and the increase of the anointing.

00:10:17.709 --> 00:10:23.760
It seems to go with the price of the anointing and the price of walking in the glory.

00:10:32.491 --> 00:10:33.022
It seems to go through—you seem to go through the winepress where you feel the pressure of things.

00:10:38.826 --> 00:10:44.506
The character it takes to sustain it costs you something.

00:10:48.239 --> 00:10:48.559
You can't get that in the world.

00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:03.193
You can't walk in that kind of glory from the world.

00:11:04.380 --> 00:11:08.020
The devil can't offer that.

00:11:08.020 --> 00:11:13.806
What that is, is it's coming straight out of the throne room.

00:11:14.491 --> 00:11:17.949
And it was all bought and paid for by the blood of Jesus, folks.

00:11:17.949 --> 00:11:24.448
But I'm telling you, there is a price to pay for the anointing.

00:11:24.448 --> 00:11:29.821
There is a price to pay for walking in the glory.

00:11:33.200 --> 00:11:33.640
It comes through pressure.

00:11:49.067 --> 00:11:49.480
It comes through the refiner's fire.

00:11:54.539 --> 00:11:54.880
And most people don't want to hear that.

00:11:54.880 --> 00:12:03.074
But I've studied and I've looked at every single person that has walked in a great anointing, and they've all had a refiner's fire.

00:12:03.074 --> 00:12:12.980
They've all had pressure on them to the point where I thought, 'Does it look like they could make it out of it?

00:12:12.980 --> 00:12:28.600
' where your head is pulled underneath that water and you're grasping for air, and all you want and all you think about is just to get your next breath.

00:12:48.446 --> 00:12:48.697
It comes out of that pressure.

00:12:48.697 --> 00:12:50.800
How bad do you want change?

00:12:50.800 --> 00:12:52.928
How bad do you want the glory?

00:12:52.928 --> 00:12:55.848
How bad do you want the anointing on your life?

00:12:55.848 --> 00:12:58.675
It comes through something: the press, an oil press.

00:12:58.675 --> 00:13:09.851
Like whenever you see those olive oil presses and they're pressing that oil, and the more that oil presses down on there and clamps down on there, it presses all that good oil out of those olives.

00:13:09.851 --> 00:13:12.370
That's the way it is with you.

00:13:12.370 --> 00:13:15.872
Staying on the potter's wheel, staying on that wheel, dying to self.

00:13:15.872 --> 00:13:18.760
He's the potter, we're the clay.

00:13:18.760 --> 00:13:25.946
We have this treasure in earthen vessels, that the excellency of the power will be known of him and not of us.

00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:31.371
I'm so desperate, and I thought, 'Why do I want so badly the anointing?

00:13:31.371 --> 00:13:33.880
Why do I want to see that?

00:13:33.880 --> 00:13:35.180
Is it for self-glory?

00:13:35.180 --> 00:13:36.420
' No.

00:13:36.420 --> 00:13:44.533
My heart, when I see children with special needs like my Megan, who is overcoming—she's getting better and better every day.

00:13:44.533 --> 00:13:46.560
When I see that, you feel helpless without it.

00:13:51.600 --> 00:13:53.200
There's nothing you can do in the natural to fix it other than the anointing and a prayer.

00:13:53.200 --> 00:13:58.240
So the more I see it, it comes out of my spirit.

00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:12.611
It comes out of my spirit to see children of Down's and to know that there's more, that God is a God that is able to heal, that he is a rewarder of those that diligently seek him.

00:14:12.611 --> 00:14:23.820
It's like when I, one person, sowed a seed, and I sowed it by faith, but it was a sacrificial seed for Diana and me.

00:14:23.820 --> 00:14:25.440
We did it recently.

00:14:32.580 --> 00:14:32.910
And they said, 'Well, we're believing for a hundredfold return.

00:14:32.910 --> 00:14:38.873
' And I said, 'But what I want is not monetary.

00:14:38.873 --> 00:14:50.120
' Truly, I try to stretch myself to believe for more because I know what it takes to have a staff, to hire somebody to help us.

00:14:54.200 --> 00:15:08.870
And that's going to take a lot of money to go and say, 'Well, I'm going to relieve Diana of all this pressure on Diana to answer all these emails and all this stuff all the time so she can focus on other things, to hire an employee.

00:15:08.870 --> 00:15:10.720
' Well, that's going to take money.

00:15:10.720 --> 00:15:13.973
Well, that stretches me.

00:15:31.519 --> 00:15:31.959
So I have to believe more, to believe God for somebody else's salary because they're dependent on you for their check.

00:15:47.935 --> 00:15:48.310
But the whole part of what I'm after is not money.

00:16:10.360 --> 00:16:11.240
I'm after God, and I want him.

00:16:25.338 --> 00:16:25.680
And in him, I want the anointing so bad, and I go, 'Lord, there's a balance of everything.

00:16:25.680 --> 00:16:29.759
' But I'm like, 'Man, don't you all understand what I'm saying?

00:16:29.759 --> 00:16:32.507
' I say, 'You just want to see the dead raised?

00:16:32.809 --> 00:16:34.933
You just want to see blinded eyes open.

00:16:35.751 --> 00:16:36.720
You want to see ears pop open.

00:16:38.856 --> 00:16:39.314
You want to see people get out of wheelchairs.

00:16:39.314 --> 00:16:43.360
' But you say, 'Well, Brandon, I've never seen that before.

00:16:43.360 --> 00:16:45.714
' But I know that it exists.

00:16:45.714 --> 00:16:47.840
There's a level of the anointing that I know exists.

00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:54.170
I've experienced it, but to maintain it and keep it and not get into the flesh...

00:16:57.719 --> 00:17:01.920
Like certain preachers that I've seen on platforms, they had a great anointing, but it seems like they've lost it now.

00:17:01.920 --> 00:17:03.759
It's not as strong, definitely.

00:17:03.759 --> 00:17:07.120
And I've seen a lot of them, and you go, 'Where's that fire?

00:17:07.120 --> 00:17:08.080
What happened?

00:17:13.280 --> 00:17:13.539
You had it in the '90s.

00:17:13.799 --> 00:17:19.666
You had it in the early 2000s, but then it just kind of died.

00:17:19.666 --> 00:17:27.091
' I don't want to be a flame that shrivels up, that goes away, that gets put out.

00:17:34.080 --> 00:17:34.510
I want to live long and finish strong.

00:17:34.510 --> 00:17:53.266
But I've told the Lord many times, if I'm not able to handle this, if I'm not able to preach the gospel to the nations and I'm going to stumble and fall like some of these people through trials—their moral failures or whatever.

00:17:58.092 --> 00:17:58.464
And you see what happened even in our old church.

00:17:58.464 --> 00:18:00.696
So many people were hurt.

00:18:00.696 --> 00:18:04.169
So many people turned away from the Lord.

00:18:04.169 --> 00:18:18.091
When you see a moral failure, when you see these things, if I'm not able to handle it, and I don't want to ever be arrogant and say that I am able to...

00:18:18.091 --> 00:18:26.132
'Oh, that would never happen to me,' because you see some of the greatest fall.

00:18:26.346 --> 00:18:30.860
I said, 'Lord, I'd rather not have it at all than cause a million people to fall.

00:18:30.860 --> 00:18:37.640
' That's what I'm trying to tell y'all, because of something that I don't see in myself.

00:18:42.085 --> 00:18:51.640
So I examine myself every day like that, because I see people on huge platforms that get really big, get a lot of money, and then they're ruined by it.

00:18:55.531 --> 00:18:55.897
I can name a bunch of them right now.

00:19:14.114 --> 00:19:14.389
But I don't judge them.

00:19:24.015 --> 00:19:24.309
I just don't want to be accountable for hurting people like that.

00:19:24.309 --> 00:19:25.782
Does that make sense?

00:19:25.782 --> 00:19:32.467
It's important to me to always be transparent, always be a person that...

00:19:32.467 --> 00:19:35.420
we all have stuff we're going through, folks.

00:19:35.420 --> 00:19:36.319
We're always...

00:19:37.203 --> 00:19:37.771
but I'm just me.

00:19:38.340 --> 00:19:43.340
I don't want to ever be exalted like you look at a celebrity.

00:19:55.274 --> 00:19:56.017
I'm just me.

00:19:56.017 --> 00:20:15.290
Now, I know there are certain lines when you show up at my PO box and you camp outside—like I'm mentioning somebody right now—and you demand to want to pray for my little girl and you say that God sent you to pray for her.

00:20:16.647 --> 00:20:35.799
And then you sit out there and you creep out the postal workers so much that they said if you show up again, they're calling the cops because you think that God's called you.

00:20:35.799 --> 00:20:38.320
Now, folks, I don't want to be...

00:20:38.320 --> 00:20:45.607
there's some weirdness out here in the body of Christ.

00:20:45.607 --> 00:20:49.079
There needs to be some stability.

00:20:49.079 --> 00:20:51.839
And I feel like it's not taught.

00:21:01.165 --> 00:21:01.416
You just don't go trying to lay hands on people's kids thinking because you feel like God's called you to.

00:21:01.416 --> 00:21:02.891
God didn't tell me that.

00:21:10.059 --> 00:21:17.537
And I don't know why I get off on that, but it is something that still bothers me, that there are people that are just consistently coming to my church trying to touch my kid because you feel you have an anointing on you to pray for my Megan.

00:21:17.537 --> 00:21:19.166
You'll never touch my child.

00:21:19.166 --> 00:21:20.011
Never.

00:21:20.011 --> 00:21:21.530
That's my child.

00:21:22.530 --> 00:21:30.977
And if God calls me to have somebody pray for my child, I'll take my child to that person.

00:21:30.977 --> 00:21:37.447
But you're not called to come laying hands on people unless God...

00:21:37.447 --> 00:21:39.860
unless I feel peace about it.

00:21:39.860 --> 00:21:42.029
And that's happened several times now.

00:21:42.029 --> 00:21:51.039
And it makes me, quite frankly, I get irate when I get in the car.

00:21:52.142 --> 00:21:52.605
I told...

00:21:52.605 --> 00:21:58.400
my son knows, everybody: do not touch my children.

00:21:58.400 --> 00:22:01.245
Do not touch me.

00:22:01.245 --> 00:22:07.839
That's why I said the Bible says do not lay hands on a man suddenly.

00:22:20.423 --> 00:22:20.697
And I do not, after encounters that I've had, I do not allow people to pray for me unless the Holy Spirit tells me to let them.

00:22:20.697 --> 00:22:21.909
I just don't.

00:22:21.909 --> 00:22:26.573
I would advise you to be wise about it too.

00:22:34.404 --> 00:22:35.133
You are not touching me.

00:22:35.133 --> 00:22:37.994
You're not touching my wife.

00:22:48.570 --> 00:22:48.915
You are not touching my children.

00:22:48.915 --> 00:22:51.260
So, it is what it is.

00:22:51.260 --> 00:22:57.149
But I felt like I need to say that.

00:22:57.159 --> 00:23:13.028
So, don't come to my PO box, try to knock on my house, find out where I live so you think you can lay hands on me and touch me or I'm going to touch you.

00:23:13.028 --> 00:23:13.485
Okay.

00:23:13.485 --> 00:23:14.400
God bless you.

00:23:24.110 --> 00:23:26.089
So, you know, I feel like it's important I say these things.

00:23:26.089 --> 00:23:31.934
There's an importance of the anointing and being hungry and impartation by the Spirit of God.

